                    <msContents>
                        <summary/>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                            <locus from="1r" to="27r"/>
                            <title type="complete" ref="LIT1285Dersan" xml:lang="gez"> ድርሳን፡ ዘደረሰ፡
                                ቅዱስ፡ <persName ref="PRS10382Yohanne">ዮሐንስ፡</persName> ኤጲስ፡ ቆጶስ፡
                                በእንተ፡ ዕበዩ፡ ወክብሩ፡ ለቅዱስ፡ <persName ref="PRS4523Garima"
                                >ይስሐቅ</persName>።</title>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                            <explicit xml:lang="gez"><locus from="26vb" to="27ra"/> ወዘንተ፡ ብሂሎ፡ ተሰወረ፡
                                እምኔሆሙ፡ ወኢርእይዎ፡ ደግመ። ወፈጸመ፡ ገድሎ፡ አመ፡ ፲ወ፯፡ ለወርኃ፡ ሰኔ። ጸሎቱ፡ ወበረከቱ፡ ትዕቀበነ፡
                                ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን። ለይኩን። ለይኩን። </explicit>
                            <note>The homily edited by Conti Rossini in <bibl>
                                    <ptr target="bm:ContiRossini1898Garima"
                                        /><citedRange>171-178</citedRange>
                                </bibl>continues further for about one page, the last lines of the
                                present manuscript corresponding to line 637 of the edition. </note>
                            <note>Cataloguing this manuscript, <persName ref="PRS3182ContiRo"/>
                                noted about himself that <cit>
                                    <quote>text not used by Conti Rossini</quote>
                                </cit>(<cit>
                                    <quote xml:lang="fr">texte non untilisé par Conti
                                        Rossini</quote>
                                </cit>). The scholar adds the following: <cit>
                                    <quote>It contains the story of the serpent king of the land of
                                        Agʿāzi <foreign xml:lang="gez">ብሔረ፡ አግዓዚ፡</foreign>, but the
                                        records of land grants seem to be missing. The final account
                                        of the misfortunes that were to strike the <placeName
                                            ref="LOC2254DabraD">monastery of Dāmo</placeName> is
                                        also absent; it is evident that this is a later addition,
                                        most likely referring to the devastation caused by the
                                        Catholics at <placeName ref="LOC2866EndaAb">Endā abbā
                                            Garimā</placeName> (see, for example, <title>Lettere
                                            annue di Ethiopia del 1624, 1625 e 1626</title>, Rome,
                                        1628, first letter). Obviously, the <ref type="mss" corresp="PetermannIINachtrag28"> ms.
                                            Peterm. II Nachtr. 28 </ref> in Berlin, which contains
                                        this account, cannot be from the 16th century, as <persName  ref="PRS3562Dillmann">Aug.
                                            Dillmann</persName> believed. However, it already includes the curse:
                                        "May your offering be like the offering of Rome" (see Conti
                                        Rossini, v. 524-525). It should be noted that the <foreign xml:lang="gez">gadl</foreign> in
                                        our manuscript begins with the well-known formula from the
                                        time of King <persName ref="PRS10626ZaraY">Zarʾa Yāʿqob</persName>: <foreign xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ አብ፡, etc. በቅድስት፡ ሥላሴ፡ እንዘ፡
                                            እት<gap reason="illegible"/>፡ ወእትመኀፀን፡ እክሕደከ፡ ሰይጣን፡ በቅድመ፡ ይእቲ፡ እምየ፡</foreign> which would
                                        confirm the age of this work.</quote>
                                </cit> (<cit>
                                    <quote>On y trouve le récit du serpent roi de la terre d'Agʿāzi,
                                            <foreign xml:lang="gez">ብሔረ፡ አግዓዚ፡, mais les concessions
                                            des fiefs semblent manquer. Le récit final sur les
                                            malheurs qui devront frapper <placeName
                                                ref="LOC2254DabraD">le couvent de Dāmo</placeName>
                                            manque aussi; on voit qu'il s'agit d'une addition plus
                                            récent, qui vise sans doute les ravages des catholiques
                                            à <placeName ref="LOC2866EndaAb">Endā abbā Garimā
                                            </placeName> (voir p.ex. <title>Lettre annue di Ethiopia
                                                del 1624, 1625 e 1626, Rome, 1628, première
                                                lettre</title>). Évidemment, le <ref type="mss"
                                                corresp="PetermannIINachtrag28">ms. Peterm. II
                                                Nachtr. 28 de Berlin, qui contient ce récit, ne peut
                                                pas être du XVI siècle, comme le croyait <persName
                                                  ref="PRS3562Dillmann">Aug. Dillmann</persName>.
                                                Mais on y trouve déjà la malédiction "que votre
                                                offrande soit comme l'offrande de Rome"; voir Conti
                                                Rossini; v.524-525. - Noter que le <foreign
                                                  xml:lang="gez">gadl</foreign>, dans notre
                                                manuscrit, commence avec la formule bien connu du
                                                temps du roi <persName ref="PRS10626ZaraY">Zarʾa
                                                  Yāʿqob:</persName>
                                                <foreign xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ አብ፡, etc. በቅድስት፡ ሥላሴ፡
                                                  እንዘ፡ እት///፡ ወእትመኀፀን፡ እክሕደከ፡ ሰይጣን፡ በቅድመ፡ ይእቲ፡ እምየ፡
                                                </foreign>, ce qui confirmerait l'âge de cet
                                                ouvrage.</ref></foreign></quote>
                                </cit>)</note>
                        </msItem>
