                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                                <seg type="script">15th-century script</seg>
                                <seg type="ink">Black, red.</seg>
                                <desc>Careful, irregular; by a good scribe. <persName
                                        ref="PRS3182ContiRo"/> describes the handwriting as ʻCrude
                                    script. Vulgar forms, for example, Panṭalyon almost always
                                    instead of Panṭalēwon.ʼ(<foreign xml:lang="fr">ʻÉcriture rude.
                                        Formes vulgaires, par exemple Panṭalyon, presque toujours,
                                        pour Panṭalēwonʼ</foreign>) <persName ref="PRS1071dAbbadi"/>
                                    describes the handwriting as ʻAncient script; arabesques and
                                        hieroglyphs.ʼ(<foreign xml:lang="fr">ʻécriture antique;
                                        arabesques et hiéroglyphesʼ</foreign>). </desc>
                            </handNote>
